# Project Structure

This Flutter project follows a feature-first architecture with clear separation of concerns. Here's the main structure:

  - `lib/` - Main source code directory
  - `feature/` - Feature modules (each feature is self-contained)
  - `core/` - Core functionality and shared utilities
  - `uikit/` - Reusable UI components. Does not depend on the product's subject area.
  - `persistence/` - Data persistence layer
  - `l10n/` - Localization files
  - `api/` - API client and API models

Each feature module typically contains:
  - `data/` - Data layer (repositories, data sources)
  - `domain/` - Business logic and Entities
  - `presentation/` - UI layer (screens, widgets)
  - `di/` - Dependency injection

The project follows Clean Architecture principles.
